result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (2nd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (2nd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Casey R Enk was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

The disposition of "Other" is used to indicate several different dispositions. The Charge(s)/Sentence(s) and Court Record Events sections of the WCCA record display additional information that must be reviewed in order to determine the exact disposition of the charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine and costs shall be paid at the rate of $50/month commencing January 15, 2017 and the 15th of each month thereafter until paid in full.    There is a $15 administrative fee for any payment plan and any change to a payment plan. The fee will be added to the first payment. If not paid, a judgment shall be entered.

With Huber privileges consistent with the rules of the jail while the inmate maintains a minimum security status. The defendant, at the discretion of the Sheriff, may perform community service work as an inmate worker in the county jail and shall earn statutory good time for same.

Defendant shall, within three (3) days, contact the Washington County Jail for purposes of supplying a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Defendant has the right to request expungement of DNA analysis in writing through the Department of Justice.

Def in person & by Atty Jeremy J Guza.  Atty Stephanie L Hanson appeared for State.  Clerk: CP.  Case called 8:18am w/out jury present.  Discussion re previous motions in limine and stipulation re results of blood draw; def stipulations to entire chain of custody as well as results of blood draw.  Court questions def and accepts stipulation.  Def admits to prior OWI conviction.  Recess.  Reconvene w/jury present.  Jury panel sworn before voir dire.  20 jurors called to box.  Voir dire by Court.  Voir dire by counsel.  Jurors struck.  12 juror names read.  Remaining jurors thanked and released at 9:35am.  Jury sworn after voir dire. Jury excused.  Counsel moves to sequester witnesses; Court so orders.  Recess.  Reconvene w/jury present.  Court gives preliminary instructions.  Opening statements.  WITNESSES:  Dan B.; Gregory B.; Lt J. Gonzalez (GPD).  Jury excused for lunch.  Recess.  Reconvene w/out jury present.  Discussion re witnesses.  Def will not testify.  Court finds def continues to exercise his right to remain silent.  Signed stipulation filed.  Court questions def re stipulation.  Jury now present.  WITNESSES:  Lt. J Gonzalez (continued).  State rests subject to stipulation.  Defense rests.  Court reads stipulation to jury.  Jury excused.  Jury instructions & verdict forms given to counsel.  Reconvene w/out jury.  Discussion re jury instructions and verdict forms.  Jury now present.  Closing arguments.  Court reads jury instructions.  Jury excused for deliberations at 2:53pm.  Reconvene w/jury present.  Court reads verdicts - jury finds def guilty on Ct 1 and guilty on Ct 2.  Jury polled.  Jury thanked and released at 3:24pm.  State moves for judgment on the verdicts; Court so orders.  Counsel req separate sentencing date - will be free to argue.  Court keeps bond in effect and admonishes def re conditions.  Case closed 3:27pm.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for December 8, 2016 at 11:00 am.

Sahagian (Wauk Co Sheriff Dept); Lt J. Gonzalez (GPD).  Jury admonished and excused for lunch.  Recess.  Reconvene w/jury present.  WITNESSES:  Lt J. Gonzalez (continued); Officer D. Mikulec (GPD). Court reads note from jury.  Discussion between Court and counsel.  Jury present.  Court reads note from jury again and questions presiding juror.  Court declares a mistrial due to hung jury.
